# Layout Design

# Project Overview

This project demonstrates how to create a structured webpage layout using `div` elements.  
The layout includes a Header, Navigation Bar, Hero Section, Content Section, and Footer.

It also applies proper Box Model concepts such as margin, padding, border, width, and box-sizing.

# Objectives

- Create a Header using div
- Create a Navbar using div
- Create a Content section using div
- Create a Footer using div
- Apply Box Model concepts
- Use modern styling techniques

# Layout Structure

The webpage contains:

1. Header  
   - Logo and navigation links  
   - Styled using Flexbox for alignment  

2. Hero Section  
   - Main heading  
   - Description text  
   - Styled button  

3. Content Section  
   - Three feature cards  
   - Hover effects  
   - Proper spacing and borders  

4. Footer  
   - Simple centered footer content  

# Box Model Concepts Used

- Margin (outer spacing)
- Padding (inner spacing)
- Border (card and section styling)
- Width control
- box-sizing: border-box

# Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3
- Flexbox
- CSS Transitions
- Box Model

# How to Run

1. Save the file as `layout.html`.
2. Open the file in any web browser.

